Installing pgcli is a simple process, as long as you already have postgreSQL installed in your system. It's also possible to install it through pip, but on linux for example, there are some other requirements to meet:  Pgcli uses psycopg to talk to postgreSQL database. In order to install psycopg2, you will need to install libpq and python-dev. Since psycopg2 is a C extension for Python, gcc it will also be necessary.
